# 1. Authentication Module

## Purpose
Secure user access for all system roles.

## Pages

- Login page
- OTP verification page
- Forgot password page
- Session / device management page

## Inputs

- Mobile number
- OTP
- Email (optional)
- Password
- Device details
- MFA token (Admin)

## Outputs

- JWT access token
- Refresh token
- Session ID
- Login success / failure status
- Device session record
- Audit log entry

## API Endpoints

| Method | Endpoint |
|--------|----------|
| POST | /auth/login |
| POST | /auth/otp/verify |
| POST | /auth/password/login |
| POST | /auth/refresh |
| POST | /auth/logout |
| GET | /auth/sessions |
| POST | /auth/mfa/verify |

## Validation Rules

- OTP expiry
- Password strength
- Account lock after failed attempts
- Device registration
- MFA mandatory for admin roles
- Unique active session rules (if enforced)

## Role Access

- Super Admin
- Admin
- Field Executive
- Field Manager
- Receptionist
- Customer

